where s is an arbitrary point along the path P. The dynamic of a maximum Mt is the difference between the value of Mt and the value of the lowest point of the path, which has the minimum dynamic among all the possible paths between Mt and another maximum Mt0 strictly higher than Mt. A simple algorithm to extract all regional maxima in a given mammogram is based on the h-maxima transform [7]. The h-maxima transform suppresses all regional maxima whose dynamic is less than a given threshold h. This can be achieved by using reconstruction by dilation of image I from image (I√Äh). Let us denote by rI the reconstructed image. Then rI √∞I √Ä h√û ¬º _ d√∞n√û √∞I √Ä h√û. I
