corresponding h-maxima transformation. As a result, we get a binary image. A connectedcomponent labeling operation is performed, in order to evaluate the characteristics and the location

of every object. Since the mammograms are digitized to a spatial resolution of 0.05 mm pixel size, we can discard objects smaller than 0.1 mm. Also, objects bigger than 2 cm in diameter are

